  <summary date="2005-04-20T21:21:56Z" status="Introduced in House">Families for ED Advertising Decency Act - Requires the Federal Communications Commission (FCC) to revise the FCC's interpretations of, and enforcement policies concerning, FCC regulations on indecent material to treat as indecent for purposes of broadcasting during specified hours any advertisement for medications treating erectile dysfunction. Excludes from this prohibition the mere mention of the trademarked or generic name of such medication.</summary>
